<a href="javascript:card_browser(72)">Goblin Runner</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(965)">Goblin Bowman</a> x4<br>
		<br>
Orc Assasin x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(319)">Orc Ambusher</a> x4<br>
		<br>
Our List of Allies Grows Thin x2<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(150)">Orc Bowmen</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(82)">Host of Thousands</a> x4<br>
<a href="javascript:card_browser(960)">Dark Places</a> x2<br>
<br>
<br>
    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Before reviewing this deck, please remember this is a fun deck - i.e. for social play and not tournament play.<br>
<br>
No need to bid, let your opponent do what they like. The idea is pretty basic.<br>
<br>
1. Use Dear Freinds to place your discarded cards on the bottom of your draw deck.<br>
2. Use Bilbo to shuffle your draw deck.<br>
3. Use the Pipes and Pipeweed to heal those who have exerted for Dear Freinds.<br>
4. Use The twilight denial to make up for the lack of power up cards and weapons.<br>
5. Heal Frodo as needed.<br>
<br>
Companions:<br>
Aragorn: Ranger + Signet + twilight removal<br>
Gimli: Signet + twilight denial<br>
Sam: Signet + Pony (play pony after site5)<br>
Boromir: Ranger + Overwhelm<br>
<br>
It could not be more simple than that. <br>
<br>
The shadow is just as basic. You have enough Minions to have a swarming archery effect and with Orc Bowmen you will have some fun on top of that. Goblin Archer is more useful now as indirect archery is on the increase.<br>
<br>
If your opponent cannot stop archery he is in big trouble. At Brown Lands I once generated 17 for the Minion archery total and wiped out 4 companions including Frodo. <br>
<br>
Our List of allies grows thin serves as twilight generation against denail decks as they often have allies.<br>
<br>
Dark Places allows you to play your Great Chasm and also makes your Minions + 1 for each copy, giving you come extra punch in skirmish, especially with Archer Commander.<br>
<br>
Finally Tol Brandir is enough to get at least three Orcs and hopefully 4 archery if you get that far.<br>
<br>
This is a really fun deck to play especially if you opponent has no idea what is going on.  </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP" COLSPAN="2"><font class="bfont"> <a href="/lotr/decks/decks.php">Back to Decks Directory</a> | <A HREF="/lotr/decks/decks.php?reviews=25618"> Read Reviews </A> | <a href="deckprint.php?deck=25618" TARGET="BLANK_"> Printer Friendly</a></FONT></TD></TR></TABLE><a name="review"></a><font class="h2font">In order to review decks you must be a registered member. <A href="/lotr/main/join.php">Sign up for free!</A></font></font></td><td background="/lotr/gfx/mom/whi_09.gif"></td></tr>
